HOW TO RUN THE CODE (Step-by-Step)
âœ” Step 1: Install Required Software
1. Java JDK (8 or above)

Download & install:
https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/

Check installation:

java -version

2. MySQL Server + MySQL Workbench

Download MySQL:
https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/

Check installation:

mysql --version

3. MySQL JDBC Driver (IMPORTANT)

Download MySQL Connector/J:
https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/

Extract â†’ copy the file:

mysql-connector-j-8.x.x.jar


Keep it ready.

âœ” Step 2: Create MySQL Database

Open MySQL Workbench or terminal and run:

CREATE DATABASE converterdb;

USE converterdb;

CREATE TABLE conversion_history (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    amount DOUBLE,
    source VARCHAR(10),
    target VARCHAR(10),
    result DOUBLE
);

âœ” Step 3: Update DB Credentials in Code

In DBHelper class, update:

private static final String USER = "root";
private static final String PASS = "your_password";


Replace "your_password" with your MySQL password.

âœ” Step 4: Save Your Java File

Name it:

SmartCurrencyConverter.java

âœ” Step 5: Compile Java File

Open terminal / CMD in folder where file is saved:

Windows CMD
javac -cp .;mysql-connector-j-8.x.x.jar SmartCurrencyConverter.java

Mac/Linux
javac -cp .:mysql-connector-j-8.x.x.jar SmartCurrencyConverter.java

âœ” Step 6: Run the Program
Windows
java -cp .;mysql-connector-j-8.x.x.jar SmartCurrencyConverter

Mac/Linux
java -cp .:mysql-connector-j-8.x.x.jar SmartCurrencyConverter

ðŸš€ YOU WILL SEE THIS OUTPUT:
===== SMART CURRENCY CONVERTER =====

Enter amount (or 0 to exit):


Then you can start converting currencies.
